## Testing stack

- **Vitest** — test runner (configured in `vite.config.ts`).
- **React Testing Library** — component and hook testing.
- **MSW (Mock Service Worker)** — API mocking; never make real network calls in tests.
- **@testing-library/user-event** — simulate user interactions.

## Test structure

```
src/
  __tests__/
    hooks/          # Custom hook tests
    components/     # Component integration tests
    pages/          # Page-level integration tests
    lib/            # API function and utility tests
  __mocks__/
    handlers.ts     # MSW request handlers
    server.ts       # MSW node server setup
```

One test file per hook or component. Filename mirrors the source file: `useRecipes.test.ts`, `RecipeCard.test.tsx`.

## React Query wrapper

Wrap components under test in a fresh `QueryClientProvider`, a `MemoryRouter`, and a test-controlled `AuthProvider`. Use a factory to avoid shared cache state between tests.

`renderWithProviders` accepts an `authState` option so tests can declare whether they are rendering as an authenticated or unauthenticated user without relying on the `/users/me` MSW handler resolving first.

```tsx
// src/__tests__/utils.tsx
import { render } from '@testing-library/react';
import { QueryClient, QueryClientProvider } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { MemoryRouter } from 'react-router-dom';
import { AuthContext } from '../context/AuthContext';

function createTestQueryClient() {
  return new QueryClient({
    defaultOptions: { queries: { retry: false } },
  });
}

type RenderOptions = {
  authState?: { isAuthenticated: boolean; isLoading?: boolean };
  initialEntries?: string[];
};

export function renderWithProviders(
  ui: React.ReactElement,
  { authState = { isAuthenticated: true, isLoading: false }, initialEntries }: RenderOptions = {},
) {
  const queryClient = createTestQueryClient();
  return render(
    <MemoryRouter initialEntries={initialEntries}>
      <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>
        <AuthContext.Provider value={{ ...authState, isLoading: authState.isLoading ?? false }}>
          {ui}
        </AuthContext.Provider>
      </QueryClientProvider>
    </MemoryRouter>
  );
}
```

Always use `renderWithProviders` — not bare `render` — for any component that uses hooks or routing. Default `authState` is authenticated so most tests need no extra configuration; pass `{ isAuthenticated: false }` to test unauthenticated behaviour and `{ isLoading: true }` to test the loading/spinner state.

## MSW setup

Define handlers that mirror the backend API contract.

```ts
// src/__mocks__/handlers.ts
import { http, HttpResponse } from 'msw';

export const handlers = [
  http.get('/api/recipes', () =>
    HttpResponse.json([{ id: 1, title: 'Chicken Taco', servings: 4 }])
  ),
  http.delete('/api/recipes/:id', () => new HttpResponse(null, { status: 204 })),
];
```

```ts
// src/__mocks__/server.ts
import { setupServer } from 'msw/node';
import { handlers } from './handlers';

export const server = setupServer(...handlers);
```

```ts
// vitest.setup.ts  (project root)
import { server } from './src/__mocks__/server';
beforeAll(() => server.listen());
afterEach(() => server.resetHandlers());
afterAll(() => server.close());
```

Override handlers per-test using `server.use(...)` for error or edge-case scenarios.

## Assertions

- Assert what the user sees — rendered text, presence of elements, ARIA roles.
- Use `screen.getByRole`, `screen.getByText`, `screen.getByLabelText` — not `getByTestId` unless no accessible alternative exists.
- Assert HTTP status effects: after a successful delete, assert the item is gone from the list.
- For mutations, wait for async side effects with `waitFor` or `findBy*` queries.

```tsx
it('removes a recipe after deletion', async () => {
  renderWithProviders(<RecipesPage />);
  const deleteButton = await screen.findByRole('button', { name: /delete chicken taco/i });
  await userEvent.click(deleteButton);
  await waitFor(() =>
    expect(screen.queryByText('Chicken Taco')).not.toBeInTheDocument()
  );
});
```

## Running tests

```bash
npm run test          # watch mode
npm run test:run      # CI / single pass
npm run test:coverage # with coverage report
```

## Do not

- Do not make real HTTP requests in tests — always use MSW.
- Do not assert on internal state, hook internals, or implementation details.
- Do not use `act()` directly — prefer `waitFor` or `findBy*` which handle async automatically.
- Do not use `getByTestId` when an accessible query (`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`) works.
- Do not share a `QueryClient` instance between tests — create a fresh one per test.
